Convert a list of features to a feature collection.

Args:
    features: a list of Geojson features.

Returns:
    A Geojson feature collection.

!!! Example
    ```python
    >>> features = [
        {
            'type': 'Feature',
            'geometry': {
                'type': 'Point',
                'coordinates': [-79.0, -3.0]},
                'id': '1',
            }
        },
        {
            'type': 'Feature',
            'geometry': {
                'type': 'Point',
                'coordinates': [-79.0, -3.0]},
                'id': '2',
            }
        }
    ]
    >>> features_to_feature_collection(features)
    {
        'type': 'FeatureCollection',
        'features': [
            {
                'type': 'Feature',
                'geometry': {
                    'type': 'Point',
                    'coordinates': [-79.0, -3.0]},
